ZH: 他们之间互相推诿，导致问题无法解决。
EN: They blame each other, making it impossible to solve the problem.

ZH: 公司员工们互相推诿责任，没有人敢承担错误。
EN: The employees in the company shift blame to each other, no one dares to take responsibility for the mistake.

ZH: 在团队中，互相推诿会破坏团结和信任。
EN: In a team, blaming each other will destroy unity and trust.

ZH: 孩子之间经常互相推诿，不愿承认自己的错误。
EN: Children often blame each other and refuse to admit their mistakes.

ZH: 当面对挑战时，我们不能互相推诿，而应该团结一致。
EN: When facing challenges, we should not blame each other, but unite.

ZH: 互相推诿只会增加矛盾，对解决问题没有帮助。
EN: Blaming each other will only increase conflicts and not help solve the problem.

ZH: 兄弟姐妹之间常常互相推诿，争执不断。
EN: Siblings often blame each other, leading to constant quarrels.

ZH: 老师教育学生不要互相推诿，应该勇于承担责任。
EN: Teachers educate students not to blame each other, but to take responsibility courageously.

ZH: 团队合作时，互相推诿是不能容忍的行为。
EN: In teamwork, blaming each other is an intolerable behavior.

ZH: 在工作中，互相推诿会影响整个团队的效率。
EN: Blaming each other at work will affect the efficiency of the whole team.

ZH: 亲戚之间互相推诿，关系变得紧张起来。
EN: Relatives blame each other, making the relationship tense.

ZH: 老板不允许员工互相推诿，要求他们共同承担责任。
EN: The boss does not allow employees to shift blame to each other, but requires them to take responsibility together.

ZH: 学生在考试中互相推诿作弊，没有人肯承认错误。
EN: Students blame each other for cheating in exams, and no one is willing to admit their mistake.

ZH: 吵架时，夫妻之间互相推诿，情绪更加失控。
EN: When quarreling, couples blame each other, leading to even more out-of-control emotions.

ZH: 教育孩子不要互相推诿，能够培养他们的责任感。
EN: Educating children not to blame each other can foster their sense of responsibility.

ZH: 在合作项目中，互相推诿会让合作变得困难。
EN: Blaming each other in a collaborative project will make cooperation difficult.

ZH: 导演不允许演员们互相推诿，要求他们团结合作。
EN: The director does not allow actors to blame each other, but requires them to work together.

ZH: 班级中学生之间互相推诿，导致氛围紧张不安。
EN: Students in the class shift blame to each other, leading to a tense atmosphere.

ZH: 在家庭中，互相推诿只会加深矛盾，破坏和谐氛围。
EN: In a family, blaming each other will only deepen conflicts and disrupt the harmonious atmosphere.

ZH: 互相推诿只会让问题变得更加复杂，无法得到解决。
EN: Blaming each other will only make the problem more complicated and not be solved.
